title: Almost 10 million pounds of meat recalled in US after listeria risk
description: BrucePac recalls 9.9 million pounds of ready-to-eat meat and poultry products due to potential listeria contamination discovered during USDA testing. Though no illnesses are reported yet, symptoms can take up to 10 weeks to appear. The affected items were distributed nationwide, and the USDA advises disposal or return of these products.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Donald Trump's youngest daughter Tiffany is pregnant, former president says
description: Tiffany Trump, daughter of Donald Trump and Marla Maples, is expecting her first child with husband Michael Boulos. Raised in California, she graduated from Georgetown Law. Known for her low profile, Tiffany supported her father during his presidency and in legal matters. Michael, born in Lebanon, aids Trump’s reelection efforts, engaging with Arab and Muslim American leaders.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Colorado gold mine: 1 dead, 12 trapped after elevator malfunction
description: A fatal accident at Colorado's Mollie Kathleen Gold Mine left one person dead and 12 trapped after an elevator failure. Eleven others were rescued. Emergency crews are working to repair the elevator to reach the remaining trapped individuals. Rescuers maintain radio contact and are prepared for a rope rescue if necessary.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Trump’s Flagrant podcast appearance hits 1.5m views, outdoing Harris' media blitz
description: As the US presidential election approaches, Kamala Harris and Donald Trump intensify media engagements. Harris appears on popular shows like The Late Show and Call Her Daddy, while Trump features on the Flagrant podcast. Trump's interview garners more views quickly. Polls indicate a tight race, with Harris slightly leading Trump.
author: TOI World Desk

title: 'Get a life, man': Biden fires back at Trump over hurricane misinformation
description: President Biden rebukes former President Trump, urging him to prioritize aiding hurricane victims after allegations of a slow federal response. Biden highlights ongoing federal support and denounces misinformation. He praises Floridians for following evacuation orders and warns of remaining dangers post-Hurricane Milton.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Pakistan: Islamabad, Rawalpindi to shut businesses for five days ahead of SCO summit
description: Islamabad and Rawalpindi will shut down businesses and several public services from October 12 to 16 for security reasons ahead of the SCO summit. The event will see leaders like China's Premier Li Qiang and India's Foreign Minister S. Jaishankar, marking his first visit to Pakistan.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Trump proposes new tax breaks, promises to end double taxation for Americans abroad
description: Donald Trump announced tax break proposals, including making car loan interest tax-deductible and ending double taxation for Americans abroad, aimed at swaying voters in key states. Economists are skeptical about funding and benefits, pointing to a potential increase in national debt. Audience reactions were mixed, reflecting varying opinions on his financial strategies.
author: TOI World Desk

title: New York man killed by a group of dogs in backyard
description: A 59-year-old man was killed by a group of dogs in Schenectady. Officers found James Provost being attacked by eight to nine mixed-breed pit bull dogs and one officer discharged his weapon to stop the attack. Authorities removed 24 dogs from the residence.
author: TOI World Desk

title: 'She has no role...': What Florida governor DeSantis said about Harris's involvement in hurricane response
description: Florida governor Ron DeSantis criticised Kamala Harris for attempting to involve herself in the hurricane response, stating she has no role in it. DeSantis emphasised his collaboration with President Joe Biden and FEMA, accusing Harris of politicising the disaster for her campaign.
author: TOI World Desk

title: TD Bank pleads guilty to money laundering violations, agrees to $3 billion penalty
description: TD Bank, the largest bank to date to admit to US Bank Secrecy Act violations, pleads guilty to money laundering-related charges and agrees to $3 billion in penalties. The Justice Department cites pervasive compliance failures over a decade. An asset cap limits TD's US operations, and CEO Bharat Masrani plans to retire, taking responsibility for the issues.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Has Kate Middleton given up on reuniting Prince William and Prince Harry? What royal experts say
description: Kate Middleton has ceased mediating between Prince William and Prince Harry. After completing preventive chemotherapy, she is now prioritizing her health and family. Tensions persist within the royal family, with minimal communication between Harry, Meghan, and the palace.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Ethel Kennedy, wife of Robert F Kennedy, dies at 96​​
description: Ethel Kennedy, widow of Robert F Kennedy, passed away at 96 due to complications from a stroke. A resilient matriarch, she maintained the Kennedy legacy while raising 11 children. Kennedy founded the Robert F Kennedy Centre for Justice and Human Rights, advocating for social causes throughout her life. She is remembered for her enduring strength and contributions to maintaining the Kennedy family's legacy.
author: TOI World Desk

title: NYT-Siena poll indicates Democrats may soon lose Senate control
description: The upcoming senate elections could shift power to Republicans, with Montana's Jon Tester trailing Tim Sheehy 52% to 44%, impacting Democrats' slim majority. Significant advertising spending underscores the contentious race, while other key Democratic-held Senate seats also face tight competition.
author: TOI World Desk

title: 'Still a principled conservative': Meghan McCain reveals why she is not endorsing Trump or Harris
description: Meghan McCain confirms she will not endorse either Kamala Harris or Donald Trump in the upcoming election, citing her commitment to being a principled conservative like her late father, John McCain. Despite her brother Jimmy's endorsement of Harris, Meghan maintains there is no family drama.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Kate Middleton, Prince William reunite for first joint appearance after her chemotherapy
description: Prince William and Kate visited Southport to meet families of the three girls murdered at a Taylor Swift-themed event in July. This marked Kate's first public engagement since ending her chemotherapy treatment. The couple aimed to show support to the community recovering from the attack, which had sparked nationwide riots and disinformation.
author: TOI World Desk

title: 'Oops' moment for BBC: Apology issued after weather app gaffe shows 'hurricane winds' in London
description: The BBC apologizes for a technical error in its weather app that incorrectly forecasted extreme weather conditions, including hurricane-force winds and temperatures of 404°C. The Met Office provides accurate updates, noting the UK's expected weather and ruling out the current possibility of hurricane impacts.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Taiwan’s president signals he’ll stand up to China challenge
description: Taiwan President Lai Ching-te vowed to combat challenges from China, affirming Taiwan’s sovereignty during his National Day speech. He emphasized maintaining peace and stability in the Taiwan Strait while expressing willingness to collaborate on various issues, including climate change. Lai also addressed high housing prices, promising measures to control the market.

title: UK Rapper and influencer Yung Filly arrested over rape and assault allegations in Australia
description: British rapper Yung Filly, facing serious charges of rape and assault, appeared in a Perth court. His bail was contested due to his extensive social media following and financial resources, raising concerns about witness interference and flight risk. A decision on bail is pending, with proposed measures to restrict social media activity.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Teachers in Texas use sleeping patches on 4-year-olds
description: Two teachers at Northgate Crossing Elementary in Texas were removed and are under police investigation after allegedly using melatonin-infused stickers to calm students. Parents reported disrupted sleeping patterns and other issues in their children. The school has placed the teachers and two paraprofessionals on administrative leave and confirmed the violation of medication policy.
author: TOI World Desk

title: 'It's a live broadcast': Harris stumbles during hurricane Milton meeting; MAGA says 'total incompetence'
description: US Vice President Kamala Harris faces criticism after a Hurricane Milton briefing with FEMA, where she appeared to struggle during a live broadcast. Harris, along with President Joe Biden, was updated on the hurricane's forecast and potential impacts in Florida. MAGA supporters criticized her, citing apparent signs of unpreparedness and reliance on notes.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Mozambique ruling party likely to win elections despite dissatisfied youth
description: Venâncio Mondlane is enthusing young voters in presidential elections but Frelimo’s Daniel Chapo still likely winnerMozambicans go to the polls on Wednesday in elections that the ruling Frelimo party is expected to win easily, even as an outsider candidate is shaking up the presidential race and winning over young voters in a country where the median age is just 17.Frelimo has ruled the southern African country since the end of Portuguese colonial rule in 1975. For the first time, it is fielding a presidential candidate born after independence, Daniel Chapo, a provincial governor who was relatively unknown until being picked in May as the candidate to succeed the outgoing president, Filipe Nyusi. title: Tunisia’s president wins landslide second term after cracking down on opponents
description: Kais Saied secured 90.7% of the vote in election on a turnout of just 27.7%, after detaining rival Ayachi ZammelTunisia’s president, Kais Saied, has secured a second five-year term with a landslide victory, although the election had one of the lowest turnouts in the north African country’s history.The Independent High Authority for Elections (ISIE) declared on Monday evening that Saied had won 90.7% of the vote in Sunday’s election, on a turnout of 27.7%. title: Suddenly, all MPs know where the Chagos Islands are and what’s best for them | John Crace
description: Many who last week couldn’t have got within 500 miles of Mauritius on a map now can’t bear it taking the archipelagoWhat a difference a week makes. Just last Wednesday, you could have put money on most MPs being totally clueless about the exact location of the Chagos Islands. Give them a map and many would have better luck being blindfolded.Even a hint wouldn’t have made much difference. Are they east, west, south or north of Mauritius? To be in with a shout, you have to know where Mauritius is. And most MPs wouldn’t get within 500 miles. The Indian Ocean is bigger than you think. And don’t get them started on Diego Garcia. Surely he’s the younger brother of the titular character in the 1974 Sam Peckinpah film Bring me the Head of Alfredo Garcia.A year in Westminster: John Crace, Marina Hyde and Pippa CrerarOn Tuesday 3 December, join Crace, Hyde and Crerar as they look back at a political year like no other, live at the Barbican in London and livestreamed globally. Book tickets here or at guardian.liveTaking the Lead by John Crace is published by Little, Brown (£18.99). To support the Guardian and Observer, order your copy at guardianbookshop.com. Delivery charges may apply. Continue reading...

title: Lammy defends Chagos deal, saying it saves important UK-US military base
description: Foreign secretary says status quo not sustainable as Tory MPs accuse Labour of giving away key assetDavid Lammy has hailed the decision to return the Chagos Islands to Mauritius as a deal to save a strategically important UK-US military base, after accusations from opposition MPs that a key asset was being given away.The government announced last week that it was going to hand over the Chagos Islands to Mauritius, ending years of bitter dispute over Britain’s last African colony, but the military base on Diego Garcia will remain under UK control. title: Biden to visit Angola as global powers vie for African influence

title: El Salvador faces scrutiny for ‘political’ trial of five environmental activists
description: UN and legal experts have condemned prosecution of anti-mining campaigners over alleged civil war-era killingFive environmental activists who helped secure a historic mining ban in El Salvador are facing life imprisonment for an alleged civil war-era crime, in a case that has been condemned by UN and legal experts as baseless and politically motivated.The trial against Miguel Ángel Gámez, Alejandro Laínez García, Pedro Antonio Rivas Laínez, Antonio Pacheco and Saúl Agustín Rivas Ortega, who were arrested in January 2023 for the alleged killing of an army informant in 1989, opened on Tuesday in Sensuntepeque, in the department of Cabañas in northern El Salvador. title: South Korean author Han Kang wins the 2024 Nobel prize in literature
description: Han, whose works include The Vegetarian, was praised for her ‘intense poetic prose that confronts historical traumas and exposes the fragility of human life’The Nobel prize in literature has been awarded to 53-year-old South Korean novelist Han Kang for her “intense poetic prose that confronts historical traumas and exposes the fragility of human life”. Her works include The Vegetarian, The White Book, Human Acts and Greek Lessons.“I was able to talk to Han Kang on the phone,” said Swedish Academy permanent secretary Mats Malm after announcing the winner. “She was having an ordinary day it seemed – had just finished supper with her son. She wasn’t really prepared for this, but we have begun to discuss preparations for December” – when Han will be presented with the Nobel prize. Continue reading...

description: Former president to run for mayor of Davao amid fight for power against formidable Marcos familyFormer Philippine president Rodrigo Duterte, 79, returned to politics this week when he registered to run as mayor in his family’s stronghold, Davao city. It leaves little doubt: two of the country’s most powerful political families, the Dutertes and the Marcoses, are set for an epic struggle for power.For the Dutertes, it could prove a battle for their survival. Rodrigo Duterte is facing an investigation by the international criminal court for crimes against humanity over his brutal war on drugs, and the family needs political clout and powerful friends. description: The Sydney local health district says it is assisting the Holy Family medical centre in Sydney’s inner west after patients were given less-effective vaccines. Follow today’s news liveGet our breaking news email, free app or daily news podcastRowland questioned on gambling ad banMichelle Rowland was also asked why it has taken 16 months for the government – as yet – to make no decision on gambling ads. The communications minister said the government has “been working diligently in this space” but action “should have been taken on this some 10 years ago”.We’re working very closely with the states and territories because the vast majority of recommendations in our late colleague Peta Murphy’s report go to issues that go across commonwealth and state jurisdictions.We’re also working very closely to ensure that there are no unintended consequences here and it’s actually effective.We have every anticipation that we will be able to respond comprehensively this year and that’s what we’re working towards as a government.We will be taking advice on the appropriate form in which that can be done. Legislation is obviously an option because there is an interactive gambling act at the commonwealth level, which enables some of these approaches to be implemented.There will be penalty for the platforms just as they are now in the Online Safety Act … These penalties will be drafted and, as I said, we’re currently reviewing the Online Safety Act because the penalties as they stand … the maximum penalties are less than $1 million for some offences.They are being challenged but, at the same time, the industry does understand the need to comply here and, by and large, does comply with the rules under the Online Safety Act.
